    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "17cc3ded_5f755c57",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:29:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Your comment above for \u0027allowColorFilter\u0027 makes it sound like explicit coords should allowed on children with color filters. Since they don\u0027t have sample or frag coords referenced, any explicit coord would be a constant float2 or an expression based on uniforms or derived from the input color.\n\nOr did I not follow it properly?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba7b4426_212f2330",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:35:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That sounds right to me.  Sampling with constants or uniforms essentially makes the sampled child itself a uniform, and sampling with data derived from the input color should be fine as long as the child itself does not depend on position.  A compound color filter is ok, a color filter sampling from different spots in a shader depending on the color filter\u0027s input color is not.  That\u0027s covered by only allowing color filters to have other color filters as children.",
      "parentUuid": "17cc3ded_5f755c57",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8346db3b_2f8f5a62",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:40:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wait, actually...\n\nIf we don\u0027t let color filters read any position information, and only allow color filters to have other color filters as children, then all the sample()-where variants do the same thing.  The explicit position or matrix will have no effect.\n\nI don\u0027t mind banning them still in that it\u0027s probably deserving a warning if you write that sort of thing in a color filter in the first place, but I\u0027m not longer convinced it\u0027s necessary.",
      "parentUuid": "ba7b4426_212f2330",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dc047e72_aea425f7",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:43:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, yeah - you may be right. I kept struggling to figure out what would happen in these cases, because I kept imagining that the child would let us back to sampling something about the input in some other way, but by the time the color filter is being invoked ... there\u0027s just no other information that can be sampled (in any way) if we don\u0027t allow access to coords.",
      "parentUuid": "8346db3b_2f8f5a62",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "21635828_de82b0f6",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:50:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK: So sample-with-matrix implicitly uses the input position, which shouldn\u0027t be allowed, but it also doesn\u0027t do any harm right? Because the children (which are also color filters) can\u0027t do anything with that information. So maybe I remove the guards on sampling behavior. Ultimately, the other kinds of sample aren\u0027t real useful in this context, because we don\u0027t allow anything but color filters as children - but it limits the scope of the rule.\n\nIf people want to start writing more complex effects that do use sampling of images as tables, etc..., they can make shaders.",
      "parentUuid": "dc047e72_aea425f7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a8e91dc8_5b7ff88b",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T14:57:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right.  It\u0027s okay to sample-with-matrix a color filter because we know inductively it won\u0027t be affected by that position data.\n\nI think it\u0027s legal for a color filter to sample a image, provided the color filter doesn\u0027t know where it is and is forced to work in the image\u0027s space, not connect back to the destination.  An image as a table is okay and doesn\u0027t turn the color filter into a shader.",
      "parentUuid": "21635828_de82b0f6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a01d426c_8eb59e0c",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:01:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Correct. It *is* legal for a color filter to sample an image, we just don\u0027t have a way to do that with runtime effects - we only allow sampling shaders or color filters (depending on the top-level type). I suppose if we had SkImage::makeColorFilter() that turned the image itself into a lut color filter. Today you could adopt an SkTableColorFilter as a child, if you wanted to sample it more than once (or with some pre-transform), but even in that case, the table color filter operates based on input color, so all the variants of sample() will ignore anything you do with coords.\n\nI think we\u0027re safe if I just remove the sample-based restriction.",
      "parentUuid": "a8e91dc8_5b7ff88b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "908ea335_dcb28233",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:03:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am fine with only allowing children of runtime color filters to be color filters, but I disagree with Mike\u0027s statement that \"a color filter sampling from different spots in a shader depending on the color filter\u0027s input color is not [okay]\".\n\nThis disagreement is from a theory perspective, so I\u0027m not necessarily arguing we try to allow it now. But so long as the child doesn\u0027t reference sk_FragCoord, it cannot introduce spatial variance that is tied to the local coords. If the color filter passes in sample coords that are based on color, the child (shader or otherwise) will be color-varying but invariant to the local coord.",
      "parentUuid": "a8e91dc8_5b7ff88b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b7fb5c10_69e6c3b6",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:10:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I think I\u0027m on board.  We need to avoid any dependency on data derived from the destination coordinate where the color filtering is happening, but given that, anything goes.\n\nDoes this work?\n   - change main() for color filter effects to not receive a local coordinate\n   - disallow access to sk_FragCoord from color filter effects\n   - allow color filters to sample either kind of child effect",
      "parentUuid": "908ea335_dcb28233",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "df8bbd10_0b95985b",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:11:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "- allow color filters to sample either kind of child effect *provided they also don\u0027t access sk_FragCoord*",
      "parentUuid": "b7fb5c10_69e6c3b6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e12802c0_aa8e763d",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:15:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think for now, I\u0027m going to err on the side of caution, and only allow color filters to sample other color filters. I agree it would be neat to have shaders-as-children, if we can enforce the rules that make it safe, but (at least on the GPU backend), there\u0027s enough implicit injection of coords that I\u0027d be wary. If we do add that capability, I want to do it as a separate CL.",
      "parentUuid": "df8bbd10_0b95985b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 94
      },
      "revId": "4898f48bfd112c407e17aa07763d72fcc5048631",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "65221cba_38060da9",
        "filename": "src/core/SkRuntimeEffect.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T15:16:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m also still curious about a mechanical approach, where we just jam (0,0) into local and sk_FragCoord once we enter a color filter, for its whole effect tree.  Is that possible?",
      "parentUuid": "e12802c0_aa8e763d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 159,
